{"id": "EUVD-2025-18581", "enisaUuid": "882cf4ce-fce1-35fe-9d37-39d3b02e29d9", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nlibnvdimm/labels: Fix divide error in nd_label_data_init()\n\nIf a faulty CXL memory device returns a broken zero LSA size in its\nmemory device information (Identify Memory Device (Opcode 4000h), CXL\nspec. 3.1, 8.2.9.9.1.1), a divide error occurs in the libnvdimm\ndriver:\n\n Oops: divide error: 0000 [#1] PREEMPT SMP NOPTI\n RIP: 0010:nd_label_data_init+0x10e/0x800 [libnvdimm]\n\nCode and flow:\n\n1) CXL Command 4000h returns LSA size = 0\n2) config_size is assigned to zero LSA size (CXL pmem driver):\n\ndrivers/cxl/pmem.c:             .config_size = mds->lsa_size,\n\n3) max_xfer is set to zero (nvdimm driver):\n\ndrivers/nvdimm/label.c: max_xfer = min_t(size_t, ndd->nsarea.max_xfer, config_size);\n\n4) A subsequent DIV_ROUND_UP() causes a division by zero:\n\ndrivers/nvdimm/label.c: /* Make our initial read size a multiple of max_xfer size */\ndrivers/nvdimm/label.c: read_size = min(DIV_ROUND_UP(read_size, max_xfer) * max_xfer,\ndrivers/nvdimm/label.c-                 config_size);\n\nFix this by checking the config size parameter by extending an\nexisting check.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:34", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-17T21:30:31", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2bd4a938d2eda96ab7288b8fa5aae84a1de8c4ca", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/396c46d3f59a18ebcc500640e749f16e197d472b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f49c337037df029440a8390380dd35d2cf5924d3", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/db1aef51b8e66a77f76b1250b914589c31a0a0ed", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ea3d95e05e97ea20fd6513f647393add16fce3b2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1d1e1efad1cf049e888bf175a5c6be85d792620c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e14347f647ca6d76fe1509b6703e340f2d5e2716", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ef1d3455bbc1922f94a91ed58d3d7db440652959", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38072", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/10/msg00007.html", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/10/msg00008.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38072"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "082629a3-bacd-3892-926a-fbbad1ba352f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.93"}, {"id": "1109c911-d3c9-3d3a-a281-5babad6cc703", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.4.294"}, {"id": "1fd82e5f-3936-3633-accb-9e1aced615da", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <f49c337037df029440a8390380dd35d2cf5924d3"}, {"id": "2883ff9b-d967-3c16-b741-c2e0821ff39b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <2bd4a938d2eda96ab7288b8fa5aae84a1de8c4ca"}, {"id": "54f4e90c-1c16-3452-92e5-610682009af2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.238"}, {"id": "62c0b1a6-5a93-34f7-abaa-3e87024b5b1f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <1d1e1efad1cf049e888bf175a5c6be85d792620c"}, {"id": "6544b778-89b7-3948-b770-2146f2f83f8c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.31"}, {"id": "7900f634-0ca6-38bb-88e1-03af3deef039", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.141"}, {"id": "88930729-a121-3a1a-bf53-4c44b015842d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <396c46d3f59a18ebcc500640e749f16e197d472b"}, {"id": "9777ccc5-91c1-362c-8d85-ef0a22d9de68", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15"}, {"id": "9bddbc2c-08d7-3837-b9ed-cfcd5fa9132c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.9"}, {"id": "bf2c054b-0917-3c3d-91a8-3876a6251888", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.185"}, {"id": "e0354f37-31a9-361e-b224-5f31f74f966f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e